                    <li>The number of meals that you should have should be 3 plus 2 snacks.</li>
                    <li>Protein sources like white meats, legumes, tofu and nuts are more environmentally friendly.</li>
                    <li>You should increase the complex carbs like wholegrain carbs, rice, legumes, beans, carb fruit and veggies (apples, banana and potatoes). You should reduce simple carbs such as white pasta, white bread, chips, chocolate, cereals, sodas…</li>
                    <li>Healthy fats like avocados, nuts, flax, tofu, edamame, chia seeds and olive oil.</li>
